Benjamin E. TILTON and William T. Plumb, as Receivers of NEW YORK STATE RAILWAYS, Appellants, v. ROCHESTER GAS & ELECTRIC CORPORATION, Appellee. No. 325. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 5, 1934. Willis H. Michell, of Syracuse, N. Y. (Charles E. Spencer, of Syracuse, N. Y., of counsel), for appellant. Killeen & Sweeney and Charles R. Sweeney, all. of Buffalo, N. Y., for appellee.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM

Decree affirmed.
